translated: Engdahl, Ragnar Volter, district surveyor, Halmstad, born February 17, 1884 in Stockholm to a teacher, Reverend Henning Volter E. and Hilda Norman. Married to Anna Nordenstam in 1913. Children: Britt (born 1914), Per (1915), Anna-Greta (1917), Rut (1918), Olov (1919), Ingrid (1921), Nils (1924). Completed high school in 1901 and obtained a degree in land surveying in 1904. Was employed by the Land Surveying Board from 1904-1909 and worked as a district surveyor in Gävleborg County from 1917-1932 before becoming a district surveyor in Halland County in 1932 until retirement. Former member of the expropriation committee in Gävleborg County. Published a book titled "The Land Surveying State in Sweden" in 1906. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa.
